"You’re missing patience in your practice. That thing you desperately want IS yours and IS coming. You just have to wait. Not work harder or come up with different strategy. Sometimes it’s just… patience. Anything that lasts takes time to create. From love, materials, and goals.

And because it can be hard to practice patience with that ONE thing that stays on your mind, practice patience in ALL parts of your life. Exercise the muscle. You have to practice it everywhere so it just becomes apart of who you are." - Tarek Ali 
 #growth #inspiration #motivation #quotes

#ITboyTutorial 4: Loving After Heartbreak — I’m usually very private about my love life but these words felt trapped inside of me and was causing a blockage to my creativity, sexuality, and feeling of security (Root & Sacral Chakras). After giving myself time to feel, I turned to my creativity to try to express these emotions and this is what came of it. I didn’t plan it or write an outline, I just sat down at my desktop and this came out. The greatest reminder of how my creativity depends on the healing of self, and others. My art and work will always be to heal. I hope this message heals you, in the same way it healed me. Don’t let the fear win, you deserve love! 
🤍 #love #dating #relationships #itboytutorials #inspiration #motivation #quotes

Hope this helps someone! Your mind does not have to control you ❤️ #mentalhealth #psychology #selfhelp

You are not your thoughts. You are the thoughts you implement and respond to. Identifying with every thought that passes through your head leads to self-criticism/judgment, which always results in a storm of self-shame. Just bc you thought it does not mean that’s what you believe

go easy on yourself. allow the thoughts to come and go. become curious and observe the thoughts without judgment, let the thoughts tell you where your head is. it takes practice. Your thoughts do not have to control you.

example

“hmm i just looked in the mirror & felt insecure because my hair isn’t done” 

now *respond* to that thought, 

“[name] your hair looks fine. it’s just not done. you are still beautiful.”

instead of believing the thought -> self critism-> insecurity -> shame

Happy Pride and 4 year anniversary to my campaign with @calvinklein , “The Truth of a Gay Black Man” written, directed, and edited by me & shot by @shootersclubla. Just wow. This was my first major campaign after doing YouTube for 6 years and it’s what won me my first @streamys . All from being myself, honest, vulnerable, and courageous and sharing it with the world. So excited for you all to witness how I’m using my talent in writing to deliver messages just as power in my debut book coming soon and my work in television and film. Thankyou for supporting and loving me over these past 10 years. Today I am non-binary (I go by all pronouns don’t panic) but everything else still rings true. I dedicated this project to Nigel Shelby 🕊, and hoped to inspire all the queer little kids out there that fight to be themselves everyday. You belong here. 

 Full video on my Youtube link in bio.

Episode 13: “ADDICTION — Breaking (hidden) Patterns, Overcoming Substance Abuse, Struggling to Forgive Yourself” of my podcast, THAT Conversation with Tarek Ali is now live! LINK IN BIO 

After 4 months sober, Mary joins Tarek in sharing her testimony of addiction to alcohol, diving into the false validation it previously provided her. Creating a safe space and emphasizing radical grace, Tarek helps Mary connect with her inner child to evaluate what she needs and how Mary can now be the one to provide for her. Mary experiences a range of emotions in the episode from anger to heartbreak to shame, but Tarek reminds her that it is through her experiences that she is qualified to heal others and how forgiveness is crucial to the journey towards peace.

Mary, my dearest Mary, words cannot describe how grateful, proud, and honored I am to have you share your story with me and my audience. You courage is beyond measure. Thankyou for being my friend and sharing your existence with me 🖤

#growth #reflection #healing

People meet me and are always surprised at my height 😂

This just happened and I was like, “but Tarek, you love these people!!” Then another part of me said “Well then why does the social part feel so daunting ???” 

Then we said together 💡ohhh SOCIAL ANXIETY 😂😂 we laughed together about it. Why? Because we are not our anxiety. We are just experiencing anxiety. Accepting that you experience it, doesnt mean identifying with it. Making a seperation between you and it, not only helps you to better equip yourself for when it does come up, but also keeps you from having shame for experiencing it. Every human experienxes Anxiety. We just all have different triggers, degrees, responses, and needs to manage it ❤️
